caption: Food is delicious! You can order through their website for pickup. I wish I could have dined here precovid. You can still tho!

Joe was the best server you could ask for. He took great care of me and even made a none menu speciality drink based on a suggestion I gave him on the types of drink I liked. I can't remember the gentleman I met on 2nd floor but thanks for squeezing me in even without a reservation on a busy Friday night. The food tasted great, I has the beef and Lamb skewers and gong bao chicken. Only thing I wish I did was make them spicier.  I will be back To support

Vibes are pretty cool but I can’t recommend after coming here twice. Service was slow to the point they sent us free drinks one week as the bartender was injured so we were told. Fair enough. We came back two weeks later and the situation had not changed. Waited for 15 minutes to be seated then left after 20 minutes as no one had seen us. After two strikes we’re out on copycat
Amazing drinks, awesome bartenders. Didn’t even have to order my own drinks, left it up to the bartenders and was more than pleasantly surprised each time.
This place makes the best cocktails in DC. They're my favorite weekend spot. They also have good vegan options on their menu!

(Translated by Google) A spectacular place, a delight in drinks, your palate craves all drinks, a quiet place, the soft and relaxing music, the great attention, the people are friendly and attentive and they also give you what you ask for, the implements and the mandatory security protocol handle it.  (Original) Un sitio espectacular, una delicia en las bebidad tu paladar se antoja de todas la bebidad, un lugar tranquilo la musica suave y relajante, la atencion genial, las personas son amable y atentos y tambien te dan lo que tú pides, los implementos y el protocolo de seguridad obligatorio lo manejan.
The food was great they had their own twists to chinese dishes. Food came out fresh and very well presented.

Love the drinks here. I'm terrible at picking what i would like, and the servers are great at taking drinks I tell them I usually like and coming up with the perfect cocktail. Also can't go wrong with any of the food here.
We overdid it.. But so glad we did! Everything on the menu was so tasty. The cocktails were 🔥🔥!

Order from Copycat Co to support local business. Overall was very disappointed in the quality of the food. The potstickers were ok, but nothing to write home about. The Dan Dan Noodles however were some of the most disappointing I’ve had in a long time. Portion was tiny (and expensive at $15) with a microscopic amount of pork. Would skip until you can drink at the bar.

Honestly one of my favorite places in DC.  The seating is something to be aware of, as it is seat yourself and gets busy often.  The skewers are unbelievable and the dumplings I would eat unlimited if I could.  Great, laid back, almost speakeasy vibe.  Cannot recommend enough.
Food is always good. Drinks, well it depends on who is behind the bar
Doesn't accept cash

This is a covid review  of take out food. I'm industry, I love copycat, it's a great spot. But you're telling me this dan dan is 15 bucks for a 2oz portion? It's absurd. Like. Smallest  portions legit ever. Please don't  help out folks who tryna be uncool during the pandemic. Support generous businesses.
Tasty food and good service!! The only downside is the portion which is pretty small in my opinion. But nice place to drink and eat.

I ❤️ it here! The service and drinks are nothing short of AMAZING!! A perfect date night hide away! 😍 The music and ambiance are EVERYTHING 💯 Not to mention...The crab fried rice and walnut shrimp are a must try!! 🤤
So good
Great ambiance pre-Covid (obviously) Hoping they stay open long enough through the restrictions so they can go back to their usual nonchalant Speakeasy vibes.
Very Nice! Borat

Where do I begin? This place is a treasure. Eli my bartender was incredibly knowledgeable and super sweet. Even gave me a little lesson on how to carve a mega ice cube for an old fashion! The lamb soup warmed me up!! Definitely a must!! And last but not least YOU GET TO BUY BEERS TO GO!!!!!!!

Eli our host was super accommodating in squeezing us onto the books last-second. Josh our bartender/server was very helpful in explaining their unique approach to us, and wonderfully passionate and generous in whipping up concoctions to our tastes. The food was of simple elegance. We'll definitely be back.
One of the best cocktail bars in DC.  Great staff, great service, great food, great cocktails. Just go.

My wife called around 7:51pm on 10/2 and the staff was very rude over the phone telling her to order online. Unfortunately that was impossible as they  turn off their online ordering system when they get too busy. The reason I found this out was because I called in to ask why we couldn’t order $165 worth of food. They told me that because their system only allows for 45-90 min wait times they turn off the online ordering portal when they can’t keep up with orders. I find it very strange that they penalize their loyal clients that have not only promoted them, but also supported them throughout the pandemic. There are hundreds of DC small businesses that would beg to have that kind of loyalty and support. If there is an issue with their system then they shouldn’t pass it down to their potential business.
Great bao buns
Amazing food in a modern era restaurant that happens to be one of the oldest in DC.
Small plates were all $15 and great but not that small lol the salt & pepper eggplant was spicy but amazing!
Customer service was really good. Chill vibes and very relaxing. Nice drinks and food is BOMB!! Lamb soup is a must, chicken popstickers, bao buns and lamb skewers !!
The bartenders are not just knowledgeable but they are also passionate. Best quality cocktails on H St.
This is my favorite place for cocktails. The Chinese food is also very authentic.
Great cocktails that are ever changing. Amazing food and awesome service and staff. Truly a neighborhood gem.

Can't recommend this place enough! Recently changed up their food menu, and everything is incredible! Not to mention fantastic cocktails, made by bartenders who truly know what they're doing and take care with every drink

This is a nice hidden bar, the bartender couldn’t make the drink I wanted but was very accommodating in making similar drinks. The staffs are very helpful and provided good services. The drinks were also very good. All drinks during COVID are $15. I was also asked to randomly purchase oranges because, we couldn’t purchase drinks only which I thought was weird.

Let's play a game. I am going to stream of consciously give this place a rating after my main buddy and I went there this past Tuesday:  Starts with 5 stars.  +1 for location (H Street on the same block as &Pizza): 6 stars.  -1 for slower service. This wouldn't be a problem if it didn't look like a fast food place on the first level. Because it does, you subconsciously expect faster service, but it does take some time: 5 stars.  +1 for great pot stickers (But do avoid the triple delight and the pot stickers are small): 6 stars.  -1 for subpar bao (Seattle has better): 5 stars.  +1 because there's not many bao places in DC and glad they are here: 6 stars.  +1 for a great second level with sit down seating and a bar: 7 stars.  +1 for friendly staff: 8 stars.  -4 for the beef filet skewers. They came out smelling like a carcass and they were not cooked all the way through and didn't taste well: 4 stars.
There's nothing I like more then getting a nice $12 watered down drink after a long day at the office.
Good food and drinks. This place is always packed though so it's hard to find a seat or get the waiters attention.
Amazing cocktails and a really cool atmosphere! The bartenders were friendly and personable and they played great music too.
Great drinks but a little expensive
The best food on H street if not all of DC. Always packed but the drinks are worth the wait

My favorite Chinese restaurant in DC!! The lamb and beef skewers are perfectly seasoned and are EXACTLY like the ones I had in Dalian, China. The steamed baos and dumplings are also delicious. The food is inexpensive, but the drinks are regular DC prices. I would recommend anyone to eat here for authentic 烧烤!
Laphroaig and Kolsch. What could go wrong? 😜
Quality and service have decreased in the past six months.  I miss the old consistency
Groups of 5 or less. I need to be sure there is a seat left for me at ALL times.
The food was delicious and reasonably priced. Came out fresh, hot, and it seemed made to order. This place never fails

Great service when there after google a good cocktail restaurant in dc the service was great. The host was great once we was seated. Did not know what to eat. He was able to remmecond what was best to try. The sampler which had a sample of everything the restaurant had. The drink was super we was able to to get great choice of drink. Thank for the service will come back
My first visit, but not my last. Kyle, the bartender, is a great mixologist!

Controlled chaos. Really just chaos. Beautiful beverages and to die for dumplings/bao. Skewers and smashes also. This tiny bar does an exceptional job of introducing people to strange and sometimes incongruent food and beverages. This place gets stuffed full of people all night so go early or go late. Don't expect reservations nor expect even a barstool. Be prepared with the staff, they can easily make your next favorite drink with only a few ideas, just bring them with you and be ready.

When we first started going to Copycat, I would have given them a 5. Great cocktails and delicious dumplings. However, they have gone down hill. Last time we ate there, it took 45 minutes to get the food. We ordered to eat in, and when the food finally came, it was in a to go container. We opened the box to find that the dumplings were all ripped open and damaged. When we showed the manager, she said that that's how all the dumplings look. We've been eating at Copycat Co for years, so we know that's not true. We've noticed the quality going down for some time and unfortunately can no longer recommend this establishment.
Great cocktails, even non-alcoholic. Despite the great quality, the bartenders are relatively fast and very nice. Food looked and smelled great (I didn't order).

It is one of my favorite chill places in DC. Check out the board behind the bar for their current mixed drinks galore. Try their one of everything platter. Available spicy/non spicy. It is a pretty dark place. And tends to be a bit loud. They have outside seating perfect for a summer's night.

This place is an interesting experience. The space is tiny which is a little too much for me. There is almost no walking space between the tables and the bar stools. For some reason, they break their own ice which seems pretentious for no reason. I have to say they make the best caipirinha I've had in DC. It is so delicious and refreshing and the only reason why I'm giving the bar 3 stars. If you aren't claustrophobic or if you can make it there on a weeknight, I'd say it is worth a shot.
This place was the best bar of our trip to DC. Highly recommended! Such a hidden gem.

Hands down favorite place for cocktails and I would request the veggie potstickers as my last meal on earth. We come here semi-often and the service is always excellent - all the bartenders are extremely attentive and friendly, and make a great cocktail. If you aren't sure what you want, they are more often than not happy to make you something they think you'll like (and so far always correct). Though it's a bummer when you can't get a seat, I actually enjoy how small it is.
Great food,  great spot after my shift as a bartender to eat and have a drink for my nightcap. Solid place.
Cosy cocktail bar with good menu or the bartender can make something special for you.
This restaurant is disgusting needs to close
Potstickers were great. Cheeseburger bao was a little underwhelming, but I was already lit by that point :)
Favorite place to eat in DC. Get the old fashioned and share the one of everything. Get there early. Fills up fast.
Great food, great ambiance, great prices! I will definitely be returning!
Drinks were good. Prices were affordable and the bartenders were friendly and attentive!
Dumplings and Moscow Mule heaven.
Copycat is a great place to go for drinks and light fair. The drinks are awesome well made and creative. The dimly-lit atmosphere is great for something a little more intimate.
Great food, great staff.
Found bug in my food. But the bathroom didn’t smell that bad. Good drinks but the bartender was really rude.

Amazing cocktails. Great atmosphere - dark and intimate. Excellent service and extremely friendly bartenders. Like other reviewers have mentioned, the upstairs space is very small, but it definitely enhances the vibe.
Awful experience.
do not patronize this place it’s not safe they allowed there staff to attack a patron after spending lots of money on food and drinks - this nonsense must stop
Poor service.

This is my favorite spot in DC. Very much on the small side, especially if it's cold and you can't sit outside and/or you prefer to sit at the bar upstairs, but it's extremely worth it. The food is spectacular and the drinks are great. Copycat just has an all-around great vibe.

Customer service is not the best. I actually tried to order something to go and I was left on hold for 1hour and 40 min before they hung up the phone. ( I wanted to see how long they ignored me) I WILL NEVER GO BACK OR RECOMMEND THEM EVER AGAIN

Pretty crowded when we visited, it is an upstairs lounge so not too much bar space or seating, we eventually got a spot at the bar. Bartenders were very attentive, but busy with making drinks. So it took a while to get our drink but once we got it it was very good - the Manhattan was made very well. You are going to get a quality cocktail from this place.

Copycat is the whole package. With fantastic beverage options and a low-priced, authentic Dim Sum experience, there really isn't anything further that I think they could offer. Really really well done. Thanks to Adam from Bourbon Steak for introducing me!

Service was disengaged, food was below average (we got the veg boa buns and they tasted stale, flavorless, and premade) and the cocktails were very underwhelming. This place was highly raved about and rated (especially for having some of 'the best cocktails in DC'), so we had high expectations. Unfortunately, it didn't even close to hit the bar. There's also no happy hour.
Not much space to move around much cool drinks
Fun cocktails, good dumplings, and atmosphere. Loud!

Note: this was a Tue 8 p.m. and I did not go upstairs. Staff: Refused to make eye contact or speak over the music (not the bar music from upstairs, this was the kitchen music) so I could hear him. Food Selection: Non-EXISTENT The all-day menu has 6 items. With 6 items to prep and cook shouldn't be hard to cook it right and have it taste good?~NOT! My order: vegetarian potstickers and 'Sober' soup. The potstickers were cold, crunchy, and hard on the outside. The consistency of glue on the inside. I don't know how they were originally cooked, but prior to being put in my container they put them on a hot grill and fried them! The soup tasted like cooked dirt with cilantro. I spit it out in the sink and the rest of my food followed it into the garbage disposal. The entire experience was awful. Total loss of $11 + $2 tip. The food was, in one word, disgusting.
Cool spot with great cocktails. I think all cocktails are $14 a pop here - tasty with great service.

I had a great time at Copy Cat. This was my 3rd time stopping by and I finally got to sit down and grab food. The staff as always were attentive and timely and the foos came out quickly and deliriously.  Try the skewers you won't regret it. Next time I'll come out for happy hours. They really came in clutch for food after 2 am.
Great food, drinks, host and atmosphere. Overall amazing!
Great, inventive drinks. The bartenders were great and the music the night we went was great (N.E.R.D. always makes me happy). Fun atmosphere and it doesn’t get too packed for H Street.
Delicious food, friendly staff, great late night spot on H.
Beef skewers 👍🏾

The potstickers are definitely recommended. Skewers are not bad either. However, they did mix up my food with beef which I don't eat. Make sure the person taking orders clearly listens to your dietary restrictions, because the music at this place is loud. Bar upstairs is expensive but they offer very good drinks and is popular among young crowd
Great drinks. Great dumplings and bao. Great atmosphere.
I heard its a nice spot 2 get drinks, but never been there.

Went to Copycat for drinks after hearing good things about their other place, Astoria. We were blown away by how good the food and drinks are here, and ended up ordering one of everything and then some more dumplings to follow. The bartenders were very knowledgeable and offered some really interesting concoctions as our night progressed. Couldn’t recommend this place enough!
Perfect portion for midnight snacks. All of the things on their menu will satisfy your palate.
Best late night food & cocktails on H Street.

I absolutely LOVE this place. One of my favorite spots. Drinks are all $14 which is cool because food is only $5. It’s a nice balance. They also use top shelf  liquor from what I’ve had. I come here often for a nice chill vibe. Upstairs doesn’t have much seating so beware. The bartenders are all great and I wish I remembered their names because they each individually do great at making my drinks. Definitely a spot to go for chill calming vibes.
Great cocktails and excellent dumplings in a small, unassuming location on H Street. Seating can be a little tight both on the ground floor and the second floor bar area, however.
The missionary downfall is hands down the best drink I've EVER had!! 🍹 It makes me feel like I'm on a tropical island!! 🏝️.  The potstickers are amazing as well!!! You will love this place!
bartenders were great, it was a bit cramped but they made it work. I wish the menu was a bit easier to decipher.
The cocktails live up to every bit of reputation. Their hours are awesome and so are the potstickers and bao!
Perfect drinks, cozy environment, personal crafted experience. Late night bite to eat with a great cocktail done perfectly is all I need.
I tried their baos, dumplings and skewers and all were very good! Definitely going to make my way back and love that they stay open so late!
Great food and drinks. The food is reasonably priced the drinks are a bit pricey but totally worth it! Very good bartenders here and very Deaf- friendly too! Keep it up.

The potstickers are definitely recommended. Skewers are not bad either. However, they did mix up my food with beef which I don't eat. Make sure the person taking orders clearly listens to your dietary restrictions, because the music at this place is loud. Bar upstairs is expensive but they offer very good drinks and is popular among young crowd..
Great selection of unique cocktails. It gets crowded so if you want a seat at the bar get there early!
Great for drinks and a quick bite with friends. Try all the dumplings!
It was awesome the food is great. The server/bartender downstairs outside made the night enjoyable. He is very polite and attentive. Thank you

Nice small craft-cocktail bar with ramen and dumplings place downstairs. Didn’t enjoy having to hunt for the bar (the storefront is for the ramen joint and the Copycat Co. bar is hidden upstairs).  Drinks were mixed well and had some unique options for the season (Luze french citrus liqueur).  Went for a date and it was a cute place on a weeknight for that. I’d go again for 1 or 2 drinks and food to keep me going.
Super fun and tasty cocktails, cozy spot including the back patio when it'sopen, and delicious Asian bites! The sober soup is heavenly as are the bao buns!
Favorite spot on H street. Amazing cocktails and dumplings.
I enjoy making a fool of myself here every so often.

Exactly what the description says, super hip cool place for awesome cocktails and great chinese food! They have themes where they have a bunch of different kinds of cocktails made from that ingredient.
Where else in DC can you get an amazing perfect Manhattan while eating hand-made dumplings?
Fun spot to grab drinks

I came here with a friend to catch up with a friend and grab a drink and I couldn't be more satisfied. We were able to find bar seating- first clutch move. Our server, not sure of his name but he's Asian and I heard he's the normal bartender for upstairs (my receipt says Upstairs S =( I normally refer to my receipts to help me remember names) either way, he was so great! Attentive and helpful. We got the veggie potstickers and the veggie bao- i definitely preferred the potsticksers, super yummy. I sadly forget what drinks we both ordered but they were crafty and we both loved them! Our bill for this was about $42 dollars so not too bad-pay for a quality cocktail and great service. Parking , hit or miss but normally if your circle enough you find something. I would definitely come back again!!
H Street's finest dumplings!
As a bartender, the best cocktail program in DC. If you can fight past the pretentious crowd to make it to the bar. I'd recommend slower nights.
Great drinks! just wish for more space!
I love the food but one of the bartender is the rudest person in the world! I asked him to get me the manager and his reply was “I don’t work for you , she is down stairs.

Great space - love that they kept the Hubert Newsom Real Estate building. The spotlight is on the dumplings and baos downstairs. Made fresh by a hardworking Chinese couple. This may mean that waiting times are long, but it's worth it. Bougie cocktail bar upstairs with intimate seating. A little on the pricey side, but the dumplings downstairs (to-go too) are more affordable. Open late on both weekdays and weekends.

Not a dinner spot but great food.  Bartenders and waiters were super friendly.  The skewers had such great flavor.  I have a shrimp allergy and they were helpful to make sure my food was safe.  Cool local place off the beaten path.
$15 drinks filled halfway. Crowded upstairs and closed off downstairs

Wow. Was suggested this restaurant by a close friend, and it lived up to every ounce of hype I had heard. The chalkboard cocktails and the classics we indulged in we're world class. Rob, who was our bartender, was awesome and his attention to detail was second to none. Try everything on the food menu, and yes. I mean everything. Thanks for the hospitality.
Tasty mini dishes of various Americanized Asian items
Not a huge fan, we got one of everything, and couldn't really taste the difference among the pots tickets and the skewer meat was all rather fatty.
Amazing amazing drinks, attentive staff, cheap food. What more could you ask for?
The best 'speakeasy' cocktails and bao in the city! However, my favorite menu item is 'try one of everything on the menu', which is only around $30 bucks! I wish more places did this so reasonably!
Great
Good drinks
Amazing food, drinks and service!
Cocktails to fit your mood and Chinese snacks to fill your belly.

hidden gem, hard to tell it exists from the other side of the street. amazingly flavorful and cheap street style food, and $14 fancy cocktails. one of my favorite spots in dc. head upstairs for a small, close-quarters, low lit bar that provides a comfy atmosphere... or get your food to go after a night out bar hopping on H st, in the bright and colorfully painted kitchen downstairs. oh and they give you goldfish as a snack at the bar upstairs when you sit down ^_^
Cool place. The dumplings and skewers were yummy! I got a bourbon mule and it was delicious. It has a cool, underground type of vibe.
Best late night fix!
Creative and delicious drinks! The food is yummy too.
Amazing food, great selection of cocktails, outstanding service and super vibe. Great place to visit for a few drinks or proper food.
Fantastic cocktails!
If you're hungry right away , always order the "Bao" which is much like a Pork Bun... the service was great the bartenders were excellent...I'm definitely going back!
You can eat the entire menu for 29 dollars, do it!  But be prepared to wait for some okay cocktails, the bartenders are too busy taking shots.

Came here for a couple of drinks after a work event downtown. Super fun environment, great music and a friendly staff.  I really enjoyed their Fancy Burger & Garlic Fries. To drink I ordered the Tequila Mockingbird and it was deliciousssssss. I ended up coming 3 times.
Get all the cocktails and make sure you umorder dumplings from downstairs
Balanced cocktails and tasty Asian infused food. Mixologists are nice and engaging. Can’t wait to go back.

As one who normally makes his family's recipe for dumplings and bao, I can say that this is a delicious and affordable eatery. They focus on the quality of their product, and the cocktails are great too!
Great drinks - be prepared for a crowd.

The bao was good but I crunched on a piece of plastic I found in mine... looked like it probably broke off from a storage container or something. I didn’t take a pic because I didn’t want my date to freak out. Other than that staff was nice.
Great drinks and the apps were amazing!! Wish I lived in DC! Perfect spot for Happy Hour!
Expectations were blown away! So good!
Great Food

I am officially obsessed with this place. They have the best cocktails I have ever tasted in my entire life and I'm 46. Watching the bartenders make them is literally an experience. I was like oh this is what bartenders supposed to look like. And the food is really really good. All the various skewers are good but the star of their menu are the pork baos. O.M.G. My friends and kids and I went there and ended up arguing over who got the last one. if I had to find something bad to say about this place it would just be that it's too small. I honestly feel like they're cheating themselves out of making more money by not expanding to a bigger spot because it's so tight in there. other than that I live in Fredericksburg and I'm willing to drive all the way up to DC to go to this place all the time. If you're on the fence about whether or not you should go here, do yourself a favor and go.
Great food, great prices, great drinks. Go in the spring/ summer, the back patio area is nice
Great cocktails and food
Love their skewers
Great food & wonderful service as usual. Bartenders are also v hot.
Since the closing of Church and State aka Idle Hands, this is the best cocktail bar in this section of H st NE DC.

wasnt to happy had the chicken and lamb skewer the chicken had a fishy taste to it and while i was waiting in my food i saw the server touching the other peoples order of the bao and pot stickers with his bare hands not a good look they need to be wearing gloves wont be going back again

Greetings!  It was my first time here tonight into the morning! This venue was suggested by a local who frequents this location.  Sooo we walked in ..it was late..I want to say we were close to..if not midnight at this point..still cool and early for DC.  So we left this great industry event at City Winery to have a decent good time (low key vibes) here at Copy Cat & Co.  Wow. Walked up the stairs straight to bar...asked the bartender (ROB) what are his popular drinks...he immediately dimisses me and directs me to the chalkboard menu. I'm used to an engaging bartender. No formal menu..for drinks or food..no hospitality...NOTHING. ALL this so he can keep his convo going with his boy at the bar (to my left)...to add insult to injury..he furthered his unwillingness to service us..by bypassing us ..and turning his back..and not even acknowledging we were there to tend to patrons who had just arrived ‍..SMH...THEN he continues on his LONG convo with another customer THE ENTIRE time. Ignores his customers the WHOLE time..lol  CRAZY to keep chatting with his boy... I had one drink..only to appease the ladies I was with ‍...The drink was good (not taking this away from him) but his customer service was TRASH!!! annd that was my last drink...as my friends had another. JP the Bar-Back was sooooo hospitable , welcoming and attentative!!! Its like he knew the bartender was being a jerk! He smiled and was very attentive, which was refreshing for the moment...he was a breath of fresh air. I wish we moved after we ordered our items. Thank you JP!! He's the only reason this review holds any weight...because ROB's hospitality was TRASH!! Thank you JP for my well SERVED cup of water!!!  This is why I tipped you!! Yes! Customer service goes a looonnnng way!  In business..you have to treat everyone with decency and hospitality..thats the only way that makes sense...and that's what makes US COME BACK!!  I wouldn't say I would never come back..but it would probably be a VERY VERY VERY long time before I do I'm allergic to bad energy....‍...who am I kidding. I won't be back.  People pay for experiences, I can make my drink at home and save my money and avoid the disrespect. Yes I was so blow away by his behavior...I started this review right there. That's not the way you tend to PAYING customers. Note to Management.  Great venue. Bad Service.
This is for sure the best bar in D.C..
Cocktails were so good!! All of them are so balanced and textured. Illai was great

came for the food, stayed for the drinks  we came on a busy Saturday night - luckily we made eye contact with the bartender, and he showed us to two seats in the corner of the bar. It was great entertainment watching him make drinks all night. literally the best Manhattan I've ever had. we had the dumplings and bao as well which were delicious (the chicken skewer was just okay). definitely recommended!
Its a hidden gem in the city!! A  nice ambience to catch up with friends.
Awesome drinks and staff. It’s a small space though so it gets cramped and loud

My absolute favorite late night go to for yummy eats. The staff is always nice, the food is usually great. The wait time for food takes a bit long, but they make it fresh, so I'm willing to wait. My last visit the dumplings tasted a bit burnt on the bottom, but I won't hold it against them. Of countless trips this was my only mediocre experience and it was only with that one item, everything else was delicious. I'd still highly recommend and will still be back!
Super small space. Amazing drinks. Good service.
I LOVE THIS PLACE! Creative cocktails, menu of small bites, different setting (cafe, patio, bar, lounge, communal table), cool music, friendly staff. I take EVERYONE here who visits me in DC.

Fantastic cocktails. They have a list of classic cocktails as well as a chalkboard with their specials of the day/week. If nothing suits you, just let the bartenders know what sorts of spirits you like, whether you like your drink booze forward, sweet, tart, spicy, etc and the master bartenders will whip up something perfect. I try to stop here every time I'm in town and it's always worth the trek to the H Street Corridor. The Chinese food is good too!
Excellent food with Imaginative libations. True mixology here. You must try the water lily...Very tasty!!
Love the dumplings. The bartenders make excellent drinks. Can be tricky to get a seat.

I was in Washington D.C for a week came here twice the food simple but good. They have four different meat for their skewers I tried Beef Ribeye ,Lamb and Chicken get it spicy seasoned well. A very good drink selection

I love CopyCat. They do have vegan-friendly options. Their veggie bao buns are delicious! Stuffed only with veggies and noodles, with a bit of soy sauce for dipping, it is definitely worth a visit. The atmosphere is eclectic and fun, with their multi-coloured Maneki-neko cat paintings on the walls, painted by a local artist, and the front being tall glass windows with bar seating facing the glass so that you can look out onto the busy H St. The only reason I gave four stars instead of five is because on my last visit there, I went with my best friend. We ordered two separate orders, but paid under one check. I advised that mine would be separate because I'm vegan, and B had ordered a meat kabob dish. However, when the order came out, the order was all in one box; my buns were in there underneath his kabobs and they were touching (I laughed so hard as I wrote that!!). As a vegan, that made my food inedible. So I advised the cashier and he tried to just take the buns out and separate them. However, when I advised that I still could not eat them because the meat actually touched, he got a bad attitude and went and got the chef (and/or owner?), and they tried to say that I didn't let them know that it was separate.
